   9:../libs/PoliTeKDSP/libs/libDaisy/src/per/tim.h **** {
  10:../libs/PoliTeKDSP/libs/libDaisy/src/per/tim.h **** /** @brief Hardare timer peripheral support.
  11:../libs/PoliTeKDSP/libs/libDaisy/src/per/tim.h ****  ** 
  12:../libs/PoliTeKDSP/libs/libDaisy/src/per/tim.h ****  ** Supports general-function TIM peripherals:
  13:../libs/PoliTeKDSP/libs/libDaisy/src/per/tim.h ****  ** - TIM2, TIM3, TIM4, TIM5
  14:../libs/PoliTeKDSP/libs/libDaisy/src/per/tim.h ****  **
  15:../libs/PoliTeKDSP/libs/libDaisy/src/per/tim.h ****  ** DaisySeed, and many internal peripherals utilize TIM2 for timing/delay purposes.
  16:../libs/PoliTeKDSP/libs/libDaisy/src/per/tim.h ****  ** It is configured to be at the maximum frequency: typically 200MHz or 240MHz (boost) 
  17:../libs/PoliTeKDSP/libs/libDaisy/src/per/tim.h ****  ** for measuring/delaying for very short periods. 
  18:../libs/PoliTeKDSP/libs/libDaisy/src/per/tim.h ****  **
  19:../libs/PoliTeKDSP/libs/libDaisy/src/per/tim.h ****  ** The GetUs/GetMs functions are available for convenience (and backwards compatibility),
  20:../libs/PoliTeKDSP/libs/libDaisy/src/per/tim.h ****  ** but to avoid wrapping errors on math when doing time-delta calculations, using ticks is 
  21:../libs/PoliTeKDSP/libs/libDaisy/src/per/tim.h ****  ** recommended. The data can be converted to the final time-base after getting the difference in t
  22:../libs/PoliTeKDSP/libs/libDaisy/src/per/tim.h ****  ** (Using GetFreq() can be used for these time-base calculations).
  23:../libs/PoliTeKDSP/libs/libDaisy/src/per/tim.h ****  **
  24:../libs/PoliTeKDSP/libs/libDaisy/src/per/tim.h ****  ** User callbacks can be set, and changed at any point during operation. However,
  25:../libs/PoliTeKDSP/libs/libDaisy/src/per/tim.h ****  ** the Config::enable_irq must be set to true when initializing for the interrupts
  26:../libs/PoliTeKDSP/libs/libDaisy/src/per/tim.h ****  ** to turn on and function.
  27:../libs/PoliTeKDSP/libs/libDaisy/src/per/tim.h ****  **
  28:../libs/PoliTeKDSP/libs/libDaisy/src/per/tim.h ****  ** @todo Fix issues with realtime getters, and wrapping of the timer(s).
  29:../libs/PoliTeKDSP/libs/libDaisy/src/per/tim.h ****  **     - This very noticeable with default settings for the 16-bit counters.
ARM GAS  C:\Users\skipi\AppData\Local\Temp\cc9eAo3V.s 			page 2


  30:../libs/PoliTeKDSP/libs/libDaisy/src/per/tim.h ****  ** @todo Other General purpose timers
